The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | ICC says no evidence of bookmakers
                                                   ICC says no evidence of bookmakers
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The International Cricket Council (ICC) Anti-Corruption and Security Unit (ACSU) confirmed on Monday that, following investigations, it is satisfied that there is no substance to the suggestions that Indian bookmakers came into contact Pakistan players during the recent Test series in Sri Lanka.         
	The ACSU said in a statement that it found no evidence in the case.         
	The ICC chief executive Haroon Lorgat said: I am pleased those investigations have indicated nothing untoward has taken place on this occasion but it is a reminder that all of us  players, officials and supporters  must maintain our vigilance.                                                                                                                       
